[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(12) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Three years’ famine.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—This appears correct, as harmonising with the three months and three days of the other visitations. Samuel has the reading “seven,” which perhaps originated in some scribe’s memory of the famine described in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 41:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sqq.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To be destroyed.—Samuel has, “thy flying,” and so LXX. and Vulg. here. This is doubtless right, as the word in our Hebrew text might easily be a corrupt form of that in Samuel.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "To be destroyed.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Samuel has, “thy flying,” and so LXX. and Vulg. here. This is doubtless right, as the word in our Hebrew text might easily be a corrupt form of that in Samuel.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "While that the sword of thine enemies overtaketh thee.—Literally, and the sword of thy foes at overtaking. The word “overtaking” (massègeth) only occurs besides in Leviticus 14:21. Samuel has simply, “and he pursuing thee.” Perhaps the right text is, and he pursue thee to overtaking. (Comp. the Syriac here: “Three months thou shalt be subdued before thy enemy, and he shall be pursuing thee, and he shall be mastering thee.”)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "While that the sword of thine enemies overtaketh thee.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "and the sword of thy foes at overtaking.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " The word “overtaking” (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "massègeth",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") only occurs besides in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 14:21",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Samuel has simply, “and he pursuing thee.” Perhaps the right text is, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "and he pursue thee to overtaking.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (Comp. the Syriac here: “Three months thou shalt be subdued before thy enemy, and he shall be pursuing thee, and he shall be mastering thee.”)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or else three days the sword of the Lord . . . coasts of Israel.—Samuel has the brief, “Or that there be three days’ pestilence in thy land.” Our text appears to be an exegetical expansion of the older statement. Others suppose it to be the original, of which Samuel is an epitome, alleging that otherwise “the angel” is introduced in 2Samuel 24:16 quite suddenly and abruptly. But we must remember that in the thought of those times pestilence and “the sword,” or “angel of the Lord,” would be suggestive of each other. (Comp. 2Kings 19:35; and for the three judgments, Ezekiel 5:17; Ezekiel 14:13-19; Ezekiel 14:21; Leviticus 26:25-26.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Or else three days the sword of the Lord . . . coasts of Israel.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Samuel has the brief, “Or that there be three days’ pestilence in thy land.” Our text appears to be an exegetical expansion of the older statement. Others suppose it to be the original, of which Samuel is an epitome, alleging that otherwise “the angel” is introduced in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Samuel 24:16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " quite suddenly and abruptly. But we must remember that in the thought of those times pestilence and “the sword,” or ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "“",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "angel of the Lord,” would be suggestive of each other. (Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Kings 19:35",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
