      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The parallel place has, in our Hebrew text, \"seven\" instead of \"three.\" But the Septuagint indicates this to be but a corruption of a later text; for it reads\" three,\" as here. The parallel place shows no mention of the destroying angel here spoken cf. The three inflictions of famine, sword, pestilence, are found not unfrequently elsewhere in Scripture (see ",
